title: Live worm found in woman's brain
description: A woman who was experiencing forgetfulness and depression has had an 8cm-long parasitic roundworm removed from her brain.

title: Spanish football federation calls for president to resign over World Cup kiss
description: The Spanish football federation has called for its president Luis Rubiales to resign following his controversial kiss at the Women's World Cup final.

title: Helicopter crashes into apartment building
description: Two people have been killed after a helicopter crashed into an apartment complex in Florida.

title: Hundreds of passengers to be flown home after P&O cruise liner 'crash'
description: More than 300 guests who were on board a P&O cruise liner which reportedly crashed into a petrol tanker will have their holiday cut short and be flown home.

title: Trial date set for Trump on charges of plotting to overturn election results
description: The trial of Donald Trump on charges of plotting to overturn the 2020 presidential election result has been set for 4 March 2024.

title: Elton John treated in hospital
description: Sir Elton John was taken to hospital after suffering a fall at his house in France.

title: Prosecutors open inquiries into whether Spanish FA boss's World Cup kiss was sexual harassment
description: Spanish prosecutors have opened inquiries into the kiss by Spanish FA boss Luis Rubiales.

title: Memorial pole 'stolen' from Canadian First Nation people set to 'return home' from UK museum
description: A memorial pole which was allegedly stolen from a Canadian First Nation people nearly a century ago and put on display in Scotland is being prepared for the long journey back to its place of origin.

title: Locals of photogenic Austrian village protest against mass tourism
description: Locals in the picturesque Austrian village of Hallstatt have staged a protest against mass tourism by blocking the main road to the town.

title: France bans Muslim students from wearing abaya dress in state schools
description: Children in French state schools will no longer be allowed to wear the abaya, a long loose-fitting dress worn by some Muslim women.

title: 'Hero' saves girl, 3, who fell from fifth-floor balcony in Italy
description: An Italian banker has been hailed a hero after miraculously catching a toddler who fell from a fifth-floor balcony in Turin.

title: Hannah Montana star charged with theft and public intoxication
description: Hannah Montana star Mitchel Musso was arrested on Saturday on charges of theft and public intoxication after stealing a bag of crisps.

title: The 'Iron Man' device Novak Djokovic may wear at US Open - and what experts make of it
description: Novak Djokovic has raised eyebrows at this year's Grand Slams by revealing a mysterious metal disc strapped to his chest.

title: Who is Luis Rubiales - the Spanish FA boss at the centre of the World Cup kissing row?
description: Instead of celebrating its women's World Cup triumph, Spanish football has been overshadowed by the actions of one of its most powerful men.
